The paper deals with a randomized distributed algorithm for spreading a rumour in a graph, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC). The algorithm involves the use of clocks and randomization, which are common techniques in the field of stochastic processes and simulation (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the average and guaranteed spread times of the algorithm, which are performance metrics commonly used in the study of control systems and optimization (cs.SY). The algorithm is applied to graphs, which are objects of study in graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical relationships between the synchronous and asynchronous versions of the algorithm, which is a topic related to network engineering and communication (cs.NE).
